        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-12-05 15:59:50.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n@Sylvain\nI absolutely agree with you that it is a bad practice and should be avoided. The thing is that in a first step we are trying to achieve the same functionality as is offered by NodePorts to avoid some long discussions with projects on why my stuff is not working after switching to ingress and then when we finish the transition we will start limiting the ONAP exposure",
